8 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 176 IS CREATED TO
9 READ AS FOLLOWS:
10 (1) To evaluate projects submitted for grants under the LARP, the cabinet shall
11 develop a scoring system for the project which assigns a score using a one (1) to
12 ten (10) scale, with higher numbers assigned to projects exhibiting the greatest
13 need.
14 (2) The scoring system under this section shall include an evaluation of the following
15 factors:
16 (a) Preservation of assets, which shall include an evaluation of the current
17 physical condition of the road, including wear and tear, cracking, missing
18 pavement and potholes, roadway and shoulder degradation, and rutting;
19 (b) Safety;
20 (c) Cost; and
21 (d) Traffic volume.
22 SECTION 4. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 176 IS CREATED TO
23 READ AS FOLLOWS:
24 (1) The cabinet shall use the county population ranking produced every two (2) years
25 by the Cabinet for Economic Development to determine the amount of local
26 matching funds required for grants awarded from the LARP.
27 (2) The required local match for a project receiving funds from the LARP for
